WEBVTT

01:40.539 --> 01:45.850
[Speed and Love]

01:46.240 --> 01:48.670
[Episode 11]

01:54.200 --> 01:55.120
Zhao,

01:56.120 --> 01:57.630
get me the hair dryer.

02:02.150 --> 02:03.480
Blow-dry my hair for me.

02:37.640 --> 02:40.490
♪ Faded light that pulls me far ♪

02:43.329 --> 02:46.610
♪ Chase the whispers where you are ♪

02:48.930 --> 02:52.130
♪ Through the echo as I still stray ♪

02:54.480 --> 02:57.610
♪ Every step takes me away ♪

02:58.670 --> 03:04.180
♪ Away from the noise,
the endless fights ♪

03:05.140 --> 03:09.260
♪  Through the quiet of your light ♪

03:09.320 --> 03:10.000
Jin Zhao.

03:10.310 --> 03:15.640
♪ I'll break the chains
and leave the gray ♪

03:11.630 --> 03:12.630
I want some water.

03:16.329 --> 03:22.140
♪ Take me far, just take me away ♪

03:24.980 --> 03:28.650
♪ Wind is howling and calling me ♪

03:29.810 --> 03:34.140
♪ Through the forest to the sea ♪

03:35.860 --> 03:40.110
♪ Shadows dance, the sky's turned grey ♪

03:41.510 --> 03:45.250
♪ But your voice still leads my ♪

03:42.070 --> 03:43.730
You're so high-maintenance.

03:44.320 --> 03:45.980
How will you ever get married?

03:47.070 --> 03:49.440
Who says I can't be a good wife?

03:49.829 --> 03:50.490
Not likely.

03:50.720 --> 03:51.760
Why not likely?

03:53.600 --> 03:54.440
Gentle,

03:54.829 --> 03:55.760
cute,

03:56.480 --> 03:57.440
virtuous,

03:57.600 --> 03:59.110
and understanding.

03:59.829 --> 04:01.630
This person you're describing—

04:02.600 --> 04:03.350
do I know her?

04:09.390 --> 04:10.720
Even prone to violence.

04:13.830 --> 04:16.230
Don't go causing trouble for other people.

04:17.720 --> 04:19.579
I won't cause trouble for others.

04:20.640 --> 04:22.440
I'll only cause trouble for you.

04:40.640 --> 04:42.500
Are you really not going to sleep?

04:48.990 --> 04:50.190
I do need to sleep.

04:50.430 --> 04:52.830
I heard the New Year atmosphere
is quite strong here.

04:52.830 --> 04:55.150
I'm planning to go walk around
the streets tomorrow.

04:55.150 --> 04:56.280
Want to come with me?

04:58.310 --> 05:00.370
We'll talk about it after you wake up.

05:01.190 --> 05:02.790
I can't wake up on my own.

05:03.400 --> 05:04.800
You'll have to wake me up.

05:10.720 --> 05:11.480
Jin Zhao.

05:14.160 --> 05:15.840
Can you tell me about things

05:16.280 --> 05:17.790
from when we were little?

05:18.790 --> 05:20.720
I've forgotten a lot of it already.

05:27.750 --> 05:29.080
What do you want to hear?

05:30.160 --> 05:31.480
I want to know

05:33.520 --> 05:34.670
why Mom and Dad

05:36.150 --> 05:37.440
got divorced.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.550
I know they were always arguing,

05:41.050 --> 05:42.640
but what exactly

05:43.080 --> 05:44.840
caused the divorce in the end?

05:57.080 --> 05:59.280
Because of a few potted plants, I think.

06:01.640 --> 06:02.500
Potted plants?

06:05.710 --> 06:06.940
Jin Qiang broke a few of

06:06.940 --> 06:08.750
Jiang Yinghan's favorite potted plants.

06:08.750 --> 06:09.670
Jin Qiang!

06:09.670 --> 06:11.380
-Love to keep them, huh?
-No!

06:11.430 --> 06:12.920
The house is so small,

06:13.280 --> 06:16.280
and you're cluttering it with
all this useless stuff!

06:50.710 --> 06:51.750
Remember:

06:53.190 --> 06:55.190
as a man, you should be responsible.

06:55.640 --> 06:58.070
When faced with problems and difficulties,

06:58.070 --> 06:59.330
you need to solve them,

07:00.080 --> 07:01.480
not avoid or run away

07:01.990 --> 07:02.870
from them,

07:04.400 --> 07:07.060
because that's the ultimate sign
of cowardice.

07:09.110 --> 07:09.870
Got it.

07:12.520 --> 07:13.850
And what happened next?

07:14.080 --> 07:16.040
Didn't Dad buy Mom new ones?

07:17.040 --> 07:17.790
No.

07:19.550 --> 07:22.480
Jin Qiang thought
they were just some potted plants,

07:22.580 --> 07:23.580
not a big deal.

07:26.230 --> 07:27.350
But Jiang Yinghan felt

07:27.350 --> 07:29.410
they were the most important things.

07:32.190 --> 07:34.390
She never got an apology from Jin Qiang,

07:35.230 --> 07:36.430
so she was very angry.

07:40.350 --> 07:42.080
So they got divorced over that?

07:51.920 --> 07:53.310
After a woman and a man

07:54.310 --> 07:56.040
go through testing each other,

07:56.960 --> 07:57.840
friction,

07:58.720 --> 07:59.670
adjustment,

08:00.480 --> 08:03.810
and all kinds of hardships
before finally coming together,

08:03.840 --> 08:05.960
yet they can divorce over

08:07.670 --> 08:09.070
just a few potted plants.

08:11.080 --> 08:12.810
Does that mean marriage itself

08:13.600 --> 08:15.310
is inherently unhappy?

08:31.430 --> 08:33.960
There's no such thing as
an unhappy marriage,

08:34.510 --> 08:36.640
but there are indeed unhappy couples.

08:38.429 --> 08:41.230
It's not marriage
that brings disaster upon them—

08:41.470 --> 08:44.400
it's that they themselves
are not steadfast enough.

08:46.310 --> 08:48.710
As long as two people truly
love each other,

08:49.710 --> 08:51.770
they can overcome all difficulties.

08:53.430 --> 08:55.430
Where there's a will, there's a way.

09:03.520 --> 09:04.190
Zhao.

09:04.590 --> 09:05.400
I think

09:05.920 --> 09:08.720
you'll definitely be
a good husband in the future.

09:11.360 --> 09:13.160
Whether I'm a good husband or not

09:14.400 --> 09:15.660
is for my wife to judge.

09:18.880 --> 09:20.120
So when do you

09:20.710 --> 09:22.160
plan to get married?

09:35.160 --> 09:36.760
I've never thought about it.

09:37.950 --> 09:39.040
I remember...

09:40.470 --> 09:42.070
I remember one time

09:43.530 --> 09:44.730
when I was at home,

09:44.880 --> 09:45.670
I saw Mom and Dad

09:45.670 --> 09:47.310
arguing for some reason.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.260
I was really scared and hid under the bed,

09:50.360 --> 09:52.070
but you just kept doing your homework.

09:52.070 --> 09:53.240
I was so mad.

09:58.240 --> 09:59.430
When was that?

10:00.280 --> 10:03.210
When I was in second grade
and you were in junior high.

10:04.200 --> 10:04.960
And then?

10:05.670 --> 10:07.240
Then...

10:11.310 --> 10:12.400
Then

10:12.950 --> 10:15.040
I started reading a storybook
under the bed

10:15.040 --> 10:16.770
and accidentally fell asleep.

10:16.790 --> 10:19.050
After I woke up,
I didn't tell you about it

10:19.190 --> 10:21.920
because I was worried
you'd find out and scold me.

10:24.830 --> 10:25.890
Scold you for what?

10:29.430 --> 10:30.630
What else could it be?

10:30.670 --> 10:32.310
Wouldn't be anything nice,
that's for sure.

10:32.310 --> 10:34.120
You'd definitely think
I was too naughty

10:34.120 --> 10:35.580
and that it was dangerous.

10:36.760 --> 10:38.490
Truly precocious for your age.

10:44.760 --> 10:46.760
I told you, I'm not little anymore.

10:49.470 --> 10:50.160
Yeah,

10:51.890 --> 10:52.790
funny how someone just said

10:52.790 --> 10:54.450
they were little a moment ago.

10:56.710 --> 10:57.830
Anyway, in my eyes,

10:58.470 --> 11:00.000
you're like Sun Wukong's disciple—

11:00.000 --> 11:00.950
sometimes big, sometimes small.

11:00.950 --> 11:02.080
Where are you going?

11:04.070 --> 11:05.000
I'm not leaving.

11:42.640 --> 11:45.970
I didn't expect my mind
would be completely filled with her.

11:46.190 --> 11:47.920
I had imagined countless times

11:48.070 --> 11:50.190
what she would look like when she grew up—

11:50.190 --> 11:51.530
every version still carrying

11:51.530 --> 11:53.660
a trace of cuteness and childishness.

11:53.860 --> 11:55.260
Yet I never once imagined

11:55.710 --> 11:57.240
that she, who in my memories

11:57.710 --> 11:59.190
was always a child,

12:00.240 --> 12:02.170
would become like who she is today.

12:06.340 --> 12:09.570
♪ What was it that brought me to you? ♪

12:10.070 --> 12:12.070
♪ Perhaps it was fate's design ♪

12:12.600 --> 12:16.300
♪ Through all our winding paths,
we always find each other ♪

12:12.920 --> 12:14.190
I'm going to be late.
I'm going to be late.

12:14.190 --> 12:16.040
I'm going to be late.
I'm going to be late.

12:16.040 --> 12:17.430
-And then?
-I'm going to be late.

12:16.320 --> 12:19.930
♪ The storm turned to rain,
and everything was swept away ♪

12:19.960 --> 12:21.740
♪ Slowly, everything becomes clear ♪

12:21.770 --> 12:24.080
♪ In your gaze ♪

12:24.100 --> 12:26.140
♪ I found the answer ♪

12:26.170 --> 12:28.570
♪ There's a feeling so strong ♪

12:27.550 --> 12:28.670
Your hand is so warm.

12:28.600 --> 12:31.590
♪ Our story is still unfolding ♪

12:29.000 --> 12:30.530
Let me warm my belly with it.

12:31.610 --> 12:36.300
♪ Waiting for the perfect ending ♪

12:37.330 --> 12:39.940
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

12:39.970 --> 12:42.250
♪ There's a pull I cannot explain ♪

12:40.370 --> 12:42.010
The once chubby little face

12:42.280 --> 12:45.260
♪ My eyes follow you,
my heart chases after you ♪

12:42.710 --> 12:44.710
has grown into that of a young woman.

12:45.120 --> 12:46.590
Her eyes seem veiled with a misty sheen.

12:45.550 --> 12:47.310
♪ I just can't help it ♪

12:47.350 --> 12:49.710
♪ When I gaze across the sky ♪

12:48.040 --> 12:50.070
Though traces of her childhood remain

12:49.730 --> 12:52.120
♪ Not even miles can keep us apart ♪

12:50.760 --> 12:52.160
and there's still a hint of immaturity,

12:52.160 --> 12:55.080
♪ Sweet longing drifts on the wind ♪

12:53.280 --> 12:54.000
she is

12:54.880 --> 12:56.400
no longer a child.

12:55.100 --> 12:57.100
♪ I can feel you near ♪

12:57.730 --> 13:00.160
♪ Feel you're with me ♪

12:58.070 --> 12:59.240
We've both grown up.

13:00.180 --> 13:02.480
♪ Forget the sunsets, forget the tides ♪

13:00.670 --> 13:02.710
we can't lie together carefree anymore,

13:02.660 --> 13:04.720
♪ Watch the years pass
and wander the world ♪

13:02.920 --> 13:04.920
letting our imaginations run wild.

13:05.070 --> 13:06.750
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

13:05.280 --> 13:07.400
Yet I truly miss those days.

13:06.770 --> 13:09.440
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

13:09.470 --> 13:11.600
♪ The road ahead ♪

13:09.760 --> 13:11.860
Maybe I've been deliberately ignoring it
all along,

13:11.860 --> 13:13.860
♪ And every step we take ♪

13:12.880 --> 13:13.950
but at this moment,

13:13.880 --> 13:16.500
♪ Guide us toward happiness ♪

13:15.000 --> 13:16.800
I can't ignore it no matter what.

13:16.930 --> 13:19.350
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

13:17.710 --> 13:19.370
All these years, I've spent New Year's Eve

13:19.370 --> 13:21.890
♪ There's a pull I cannot explain ♪

13:19.400 --> 13:20.640
staying up on my own.

13:21.550 --> 13:22.310
Perhaps

13:21.930 --> 13:23.740
♪ My eyes follow you ♪

13:22.520 --> 13:23.400
she has too.

13:23.760 --> 13:26.750
♪ My heart chases after you,
I just can't help it ♪

13:24.880 --> 13:25.640
This year,

13:26.770 --> 13:29.240
♪ When I gaze across the sky ♪

13:26.920 --> 13:29.120
I don't want to let her be alone anymore.

13:29.260 --> 13:31.610
♪ Not even miles can keep us apart ♪

13:31.720 --> 13:34.500
♪ Sweet memories ride upon the wind ♪

13:34.040 --> 13:35.040
Zhao.

13:34.520 --> 13:37.500
♪ I can feel you near ♪

13:35.670 --> 13:38.310
I've prepared a New Year's gift for you.

13:37.520 --> 13:39.750
♪ Because I have you by my side ♪

13:39.040 --> 13:41.070
You'll be seeing it very soon.

13:39.770 --> 13:42.250
♪ Forget the sunsets, forget the tides ♪

13:42.270 --> 13:44.660
♪ Watch the years pass
and wander the world ♪

13:42.790 --> 13:43.670
What is it?

13:44.680 --> 13:46.680
♪ We've learned to
cherish each other more ♪

13:44.950 --> 13:47.400
I don't know if you'll like it.

13:46.710 --> 13:49.250
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

13:49.270 --> 13:51.490
♪ The road ahead ♪

13:51.530 --> 13:53.520
♪ And every step we take ♪

13:53.540 --> 13:56.530
♪ Guide us toward happiness ♪

13:53.640 --> 13:54.400
Go to sleep.

13:56.090 --> 13:57.420
As long as it's from you,

13:58.670 --> 13:59.550
I like it.

13:59.060 --> 14:02.500
♪ We'll both be there ♪

14:14.920 --> 14:18.430
The other day, there was a Panamera
parked outside your building.

14:18.430 --> 14:19.640
That license plate

14:20.470 --> 14:21.870
looked really familiar.

14:22.430 --> 14:23.190
Familiar?

14:23.430 --> 14:25.430
Are you sure you didn't see it wrong?

14:25.580 --> 14:27.040
The circle's not that big,

14:27.160 --> 14:29.020
and that car is easy to recognize.

14:30.120 --> 14:30.880
What,

14:31.830 --> 14:33.000
so you've changed

14:34.800 --> 14:35.760
your type?

14:37.000 --> 14:38.730
Are you into married women now?

14:39.000 --> 14:40.640
You didn't bring this up two days ago—

14:40.640 --> 14:41.970
why mention it only now?

14:42.060 --> 14:44.790
Just tell me what you're
trying to pull this time.

14:46.670 --> 14:49.750
The stuff you filmed last time—

14:53.120 --> 14:54.240
when do you plan

14:54.910 --> 14:56.270
to send it over?

14:57.000 --> 14:57.850
You're acting like

14:57.850 --> 15:00.920
a mistress deliberately trying to
get caught by the wife.

15:00.920 --> 15:02.400
I'm just bored,

15:03.000 --> 15:05.530
waiting for the wife to come out
so I can PK her.

15:05.920 --> 15:06.520
Fine.

15:07.710 --> 15:09.640
I've sent it over as you requested.

15:09.950 --> 15:12.010
Forget about the Panamera, alright?

15:13.950 --> 15:14.880
What's the rush?

15:54.430 --> 15:55.710
You've got nothing better to do?

15:55.710 --> 15:56.770
This was just made.

15:57.190 --> 15:59.120
Tastes good. Try some.

16:00.000 --> 16:00.710
Put it away.

16:02.270 --> 16:04.730
Just looking at the cream
makes me feel sick.

16:05.240 --> 16:06.240
Are you mad?

16:06.610 --> 16:07.670
Stay away from her.

16:08.160 --> 16:09.470
What I'm interested in

16:10.190 --> 16:11.640
has never been her.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.240
Then what do you want?

16:17.120 --> 16:18.310
You hate cream—

16:19.280 --> 16:21.000
so what do you like to eat?

16:21.590 --> 16:22.710
I like seafood.

16:23.580 --> 16:25.380
Want to go have a fight in the sea?

16:26.100 --> 16:27.520
But someone could get killed.

16:27.520 --> 16:29.520
Aren't you pretty good at fighting?

16:30.760 --> 16:31.790
But I can't swim.

16:32.310 --> 16:33.640
Then stay away from her.

16:34.210 --> 16:35.610
If you ever get near her again,

16:35.610 --> 16:37.070
I'll kick you into the sea.

16:37.470 --> 16:38.400
Don't rush.

16:39.240 --> 16:40.710
I have something for you.

16:41.290 --> 16:43.400
I specially asked someone
to bring it back from Japan.

16:43.400 --> 16:43.830
Hold on.

16:43.830 --> 16:44.630
Don't bother.

16:44.930 --> 16:45.790
I don't need it.

16:50.270 --> 16:51.270
Let's have a race.

16:53.920 --> 16:54.850
Not interested.

16:55.260 --> 16:56.530
I heard that Jiang Mu

16:56.680 --> 16:58.150
will perform at a charity show

16:58.150 --> 17:00.190
with Nana tonight.

17:00.470 --> 17:04.230
Let's make the entertainment center
the finishing line.

17:04.560 --> 17:07.160
Whoever gets there first
celebrates with her;

17:07.339 --> 17:08.800
and whoever arrives later

17:09.190 --> 17:11.400
stays out of her life and never shows up
in front of her again.

17:11.400 --> 17:12.530
How does that sound?

17:15.599 --> 17:17.710
She's a very interesting girl.

17:17.950 --> 17:19.430
You like her?

17:23.750 --> 17:24.550
Get in the car.

17:31.680 --> 17:33.880
Put on your earphones and don't hang up.

17:37.030 --> 17:39.090
Any other rules?
Say them all at once.

17:40.320 --> 17:41.360
No, that's all.

18:27.250 --> 18:28.510
Want me to wait for you?

18:28.990 --> 18:29.640
No need.

18:30.360 --> 18:31.090
You go first.

18:31.230 --> 18:32.880
The red light lasts for tens of seconds.

18:32.880 --> 18:35.680
If I don't wait for you,
it feels like an unfair win.

18:35.910 --> 18:36.910
Only if you beat me

18:36.990 --> 18:40.320
will you have a chance to talk about
whether it's fair or not.

18:41.120 --> 18:42.190
Anyway,

18:42.710 --> 18:44.030
your driving skills are quite good.

18:44.030 --> 18:44.840
Just average.

18:45.600 --> 18:46.750
I'm just driving for fun.

18:46.750 --> 18:48.670
You're better with words.

18:48.990 --> 18:50.720
Don't you understand sarcasm?

18:52.680 --> 18:53.600
So if I win,

18:54.110 --> 18:56.270
you'll accept defeat nicely, right?

19:00.270 --> 19:01.330
Three minutes ago,

19:01.930 --> 19:03.990
you had the chance to state the rules.

19:14.190 --> 19:16.320
Your start was faster than I expected.

19:16.320 --> 19:18.600
You have even more OEM parts
than I thought.

19:18.600 --> 19:19.730
It could be lighter.

19:28.900 --> 19:30.950
Then how would you
deal with the counterweight?

19:30.950 --> 19:32.030
I don't work for you.

19:32.030 --> 19:33.600
I can pay you.

19:34.130 --> 19:35.060
But I don't sell.

19:47.800 --> 19:49.640
My HP is 500. What about you?

19:49.710 --> 19:50.270
600.

19:50.400 --> 19:51.270
A Wankel engine

19:51.270 --> 19:53.160
can reach up to 650 HP.

19:53.750 --> 19:56.230
If you had increased
your turbo boost a bit,

19:56.470 --> 19:58.460
overtaking just now would've been easier.

19:58.460 --> 19:59.430
The factory setting is 0.5,

19:59.430 --> 20:00.430
and now it's 0.8.

20:00.670 --> 20:02.270
It could be increased to 1.0.

20:02.370 --> 20:03.500
It's enough as it is.

20:08.920 --> 20:09.690
Are those your people?

20:09.690 --> 20:11.170
Have you played Klotski?

20:13.160 --> 20:14.490
A game for 3-year-olds.

20:38.710 --> 20:40.470
Your Wankel engine has more HP

20:41.140 --> 20:42.370
and your car is lighter.

20:42.370 --> 20:43.920
If we're talking pure performance,
I'm bound to lose.

20:43.920 --> 20:46.920
I'm just racing with a twin-rotor engine
at top speed.

20:47.600 --> 20:49.120
Why are you so fixated on rotors?

20:49.120 --> 20:50.920
Guess why I won't buy your parts?

20:50.920 --> 20:53.190
They're not available in Manshi,
and you won't take imports either.

20:53.190 --> 20:53.920
Don't tell me

20:54.230 --> 20:56.030
you're going to hand-make one by yourself.

20:56.030 --> 20:57.890
That's exactly what I had in mind.

20:59.360 --> 21:00.840
Then I'll wait and see.

21:35.430 --> 21:36.640
Your brakes are very responsive.

21:36.640 --> 21:37.610
Did you modify them yourself?

21:37.610 --> 21:38.210
Yes.

21:38.400 --> 21:39.860
I upgraded my brake discs,

21:40.080 --> 21:41.230
and I modified the calipers too.

21:41.230 --> 21:42.760
So where am I falling short?

21:42.920 --> 21:44.880
Your suspension is too soft.
It can't hold up,

21:44.880 --> 21:45.640
and that causes a chain reaction.

21:45.640 --> 21:46.500
Anything else?

21:46.640 --> 21:48.470
The intake valve is loose,
and the coilovers

21:48.470 --> 21:50.600
and piston calipers are all replicas.

21:50.640 --> 21:51.800
This isn't the optimal setup.

21:51.800 --> 21:54.200
You've never driven it—how would you know?

21:54.560 --> 21:55.290
I can hear it.

21:55.360 --> 21:56.620
I underestimated you.

22:12.800 --> 22:13.670
That night before taking the corner,

22:13.670 --> 22:15.870
why didn't you turn on your headlights?

22:17.620 --> 22:20.030
Racing cars, underground fighting.

22:20.500 --> 22:22.700
Do you own that Chinese restaurant too?

22:24.600 --> 22:26.860
Who's that drunk man who's always there?

22:27.090 --> 22:28.510
How long have you been into racing?

22:28.510 --> 22:30.470
Why haven't I seen you in Manshi before?

22:30.470 --> 22:32.000
You have so many questions.

22:32.070 --> 22:34.600
Then why aren't you answering them?

22:34.840 --> 22:35.950
Why are you

22:36.040 --> 22:37.700
so interested in my business?

22:44.800 --> 22:46.990
Taking corners fast
is what makes you truly fast.

22:46.990 --> 22:48.950
Step on the gas pedal
immediately after the turn

22:48.950 --> 22:50.360
to exit the turn faster.

22:53.670 --> 22:54.530
How about this?

22:54.710 --> 22:56.470
From now on, I'll lead—

22:56.800 --> 22:57.730
will you follow?

22:58.030 --> 22:58.920
Sure.

23:09.510 --> 23:10.800
You did that on purpose.

23:10.800 --> 23:12.460
I didn't plant those flowers.

23:14.710 --> 23:15.880
Turn off your navigation

23:15.880 --> 23:16.600
and stay close behind me.

23:16.600 --> 23:18.040
You're not setting me up, are you?

23:18.040 --> 23:19.040
What do you think?

23:24.120 --> 23:25.850
Ma'am, I'm heading back first.

23:28.870 --> 23:31.000
Zhao! Driving really fast today, huh?

23:37.920 --> 23:39.800
I believe you did this on purpose
this time.

23:39.800 --> 23:40.990
I told you to stay close.

23:40.990 --> 23:42.590
It was you who didn't keep up.

24:01.140 --> 24:02.540
You need to be so skilled

24:02.950 --> 24:04.750
that your hands
move faster than your brain,

24:04.750 --> 24:06.470
making all your movements

24:06.750 --> 24:08.400
become muscle memory

24:09.430 --> 24:11.090
and every decision and action

24:11.600 --> 24:12.930
happen instinctively.

24:51.160 --> 24:52.030
Are you crazy?

24:52.430 --> 24:54.230
Do you think this is a racetrack?

24:54.470 --> 24:56.920
Not respecting your own
and others' safety—

24:56.920 --> 24:58.750
you've insulted the sport of racing.

24:58.750 --> 24:59.880
I was being foolish.

25:00.710 --> 25:02.990
I lost my sense of proportion
in the heat of the moment.

25:02.990 --> 25:05.670
I shouldn't have treated public roads
as racetracks.

25:05.670 --> 25:06.930
You taught me a lesson.

25:08.880 --> 25:10.680
I'm leaving. Won't wait for you.

25:11.190 --> 25:12.320
One last question.

25:14.710 --> 25:15.110
Shoot.

25:15.430 --> 25:17.090
Want to come with me to France?

25:17.800 --> 25:18.920
Join my racing team.

25:18.920 --> 25:21.080
Next month, let's compete together

25:21.190 --> 25:23.360
in the 24 Hours of Le Mans.

25:26.950 --> 25:27.640
No thanks.

25:28.880 --> 25:30.230
Once I'm done with what I have on hand,

25:30.230 --> 25:31.230
I'll quit racing.

25:31.320 --> 25:32.650
So what do you plan to do?

25:56.590 --> 25:58.790
♪ I mean baby I miss you ♪

25:58.830 --> 26:01.190
♪ I mean baby I love you ♪

26:01.220 --> 26:03.330
♪ For you, I'm always online ♪

26:03.440 --> 26:05.520
♪ I almost said ♪

26:05.550 --> 26:07.980
♪ I mean baby I miss you ♪

26:08.040 --> 26:10.420
♪ I mean baby I love you ♪

26:10.440 --> 26:12.700
♪ My heart rate's been racing
for so long ♪

26:12.730 --> 26:14.730
♪ Doctor, should you give me first aid? ♪

26:14.750 --> 26:16.140
♪ Waiting for you ♪

26:16.160 --> 26:18.470
♪ Just thinking about the future ♪

26:18.840 --> 26:20.840
♪ Those faint, almost casual greetings ♪

26:21.110 --> 26:25.410
♪ Why is it that when it's you and me,
all my composure is gone? ♪

26:25.490 --> 26:28.010
♪ My language skills turn
completely absurd ♪

26:28.070 --> 26:30.350
♪ Luckily, I'm protected by
my inner drama queen ♪

26:30.370 --> 26:33.780
♪ Calm on the surface,
but already gone berserk inside ♪

26:33.800 --> 26:35.800
♪ I mean baby I miss you ♪

26:35.830 --> 26:37.980
♪ I mean baby I love you ♪

26:38.160 --> 26:40.250
♪ For you, I'm always online ♪

26:40.270 --> 26:42.580
